Loops - 

Loops are the fundamental concept in python programming that allow us,
to repeat a block of code multiple ime depending on certain condition.
Sometimes we want to repeat a set of instruction or statement in our program

For example :
print no from 10 to 10000

There are two types of loop in python:
1. For Loop
2. While Loop

1. For Loop :-
For loop in python is used to iterate over a sequence. This loop excute a block of code for each item in the sequnce.
Syntax-
for variable_name in sequence
  # code body

While Loop - 
The while loop in python keep exucting a block of code as long as the condition true
the condition is false loop is stop

Syntax -
While(condition):
  #code body
  #increment or decrement
